    - [ ] Each Activity must have:
          - its own XML layout
          - its own Kotlin class
          - its own metadata footer (with timestamps, dependencies, ML tags)

[ ] 1.2 Backend Architecture (Python + Kotlin)
    - [ ] Python core:
          - backend.py (core router)
          - providers.py (per-provider logic)
          - storage.py (local/remote storage)
          - config_crypto.py (encryption helpers)
    - [ ] Kotlin bridge:
          - providerrouter.kt (bridge from app to Python backend)
          - apimaster.kt (high-level API manager)
    - [ ] Responsibilities:
          - route AI calls to multiple providers
          - handle metadata injection
          - manage encrypted config and project storage
          - support future Termux/SSH/container integration

[ ] 1.3 Encryption + Metadata System
    - [ ] Seed phrase → PBKDF2 → AES-256 GCM key
          - user generates or enters a seed phrase
          - PBKDF2 derives a strong key
          - key used for AES-256-GCM encryption
    - [ ] config.enc + iv + key separation
          - encrypted config file (API keys, provider settings, etc.)
          - IV stored separately
          - key derived from seed, never stored in plain text
    - [ ] Danger Zone reset flow
          - full reset of encrypted config
          - wipe keys and metadata
          - regenerate seed phrase if needed
    - [ ] Backup/restore flow
          - export encrypted config + metadata
          - import and restore on new device
    - [ ] Metadata tagging for encrypted files
          - each encrypted file has:
              - timestamp
              - ML tags
              - dependencies
              - origin
    - [ ] Timestamp Engine (core part of GodMode)
          - Local timestamp: MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM EDT
          - UTC timestamp: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ (always stored)
          - UTC hidden when Local is shown (unless “Both” mode)
          - Toggle in Settings: Local / UTC / Both
          - All generated files include timestamps in metadata footer
          - Timestamp engine is part of the GodMode machine itself

