SECTION 9/11 — SCREEN RECORDER MODULE (NEW)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Symbol Legend:
[ ] = Not started   [*] = In progress   [#] = Completed
[!] = Backend required / blocked       [?] = Needs revisit

Goal:
- Provide an optional, admin-locked screen recorder that ONLY records the app UI.
- Ships disabled and locked behind an admin password the user must create.
- Never requests permissions or records anything until admin unlock + manual enable.
- Auto-locks if recording and user switches to sensitive tabs (API, Secrets, Security, Admin Tools).

[ ] 9.1 AdminSecurityController.kt
    - [ ] Create/verify admin password
    - [ ] Store password using PBKDF2 → AES-256-GCM (config_crypto.py)
    - [ ] Expose isAdminUnlocked() to UI and recorder
    - [ ] No default password; user must explicitly create it

[ ] 9.2 ScreenRecorderController.kt
    - [ ] Bind to app root view (e.g., rootLayout) so only app UI is captured
    - [ ] States:
          - DISABLED (default, no permissions, no recorder)
          - LOCKED (admin not verified)
          - READY (admin verified, permissions granted)
          - RECORDING
          - STOPPED
    - [ ] Never request MediaProjection or storage permissions unless isAdminUnlocked() == true
    - [ ] Stop recording and release resources on:
          - app going to background
          - navigation to sensitive screens
          - explicit user stop

[ ] 9.3 ScreenRecorderActivity XML
    - [ ] Simple admin tools UI:
          - Enable/disable recorder toggle
          - Status indicator (Disabled / Locked / Ready / Recording)
          - Admin unlock prompt (password field + confirm button)
    - [ ] Metadata footer:
          - timestamps
          - dependencies
          - ML tags

[ ] 9.4 ScreenRecorderActivity.kt
    - [ ] Bind UI to AdminSecurityController and ScreenRecorderController
    - [ ] Flow:
          - if !isAdminUnlocked() → show unlock prompt, no permission requests
          - after unlock → allow user to enable recorder
          - when enabled → request MediaProjection and start recording
    - [ ] Ensure recorder only captures app UI surface
    - [ ] Ensure recorder cannot run in background (lock onPause())

[ ] 9.5 Sensitive Screen Auto-Lock Integration
    - [ ] Auto-lock recorder (ScreenRecorderController.lock()) on:
          - ApiKeysActivity.onResume()
          - SecurityActivity.onResume()
          - SecretsActivity.onResume()
          - ProviderSettingsActivity.onResume()
          - AdminToolsActivity.onResume()
    - [ ] If recorder is RECORDING when user navigates to these screens:
          - immediately stop recording
          - release MediaProjection
          - set state to LOCKED
    - [ ] Chat and Projects screens remain exempt from dark-mode lock and may use neon theme,
          but recorder still respects admin lock and app-only capture.

[ ] 9.6 Permissions & Safety Rules
    - [ ] Recorder ships with:
          - no permissions requested
          - no background services
          - no automatic activation
    - [ ] User must:
          - create admin password
          - unlock admin
          - explicitly enable recorder
          - explicitly grant permissions
    - [ ] Recorder:
          - never records outside the app
          - never records API keys or secrets
          - never records Security or Admin Tools screens
          - never runs when app is in background

[ ] 9.7 Metadata & Logging
    - [ ] Each recording session logs:
          - start/stop timestamps (Local + UTC)
          - admin unlock state
          - whether any auto-lock events occurred
          - which screen was active when recording started/stopped
          - ML tags (e.g., "screen_record", "debug_session")
    - [ ] Logs stored via storage.py with encrypted metadata if needed
    - [ ] Footer in recorder-related files includes:
          - version
          - timestamps
          - dependencies
          - ML tags


